Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle to sharpish turn. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Perhaps one three stamps drawn by Petrie (EES XVII), but a very common type. Name Ellanikos.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0604)
